Auto-fallback to g4f when Gemini quotas are exhausted.

When /v1/chat/completions hits a quota (429) or auth (401) failure on Gemini
and g4f is installed, route the same OpenAI request (messages + tools)
through g4f.client transparently in the same HTTP request. The client
(OpenCode) gets a working response instead of an error. The event is recorded
in-memory and surfaced through /admin/status so the extension popup can
display a discreet "↪ Fallback used" indicator. An `X-Bridge-Fallback`
response header carries `g4f:<model>:<reason>` so callers (curl, OpenCode
plugins) can distinguish fallback responses from native Gemini ones.

Default fallback model: `gpt-4.1` (newer than gpt-4o, supported across most
g4f providers, and capable of tool calling). Override via env var
`GEMINI_BRIDGE_FALLBACK_MODEL=<id>` — full list: `curl localhost:6969/v1/models`
when in g4f mode, or any model in g4f.models._all_models.

Why the in-process fallback is in addition to the existing /admin/mode HTTP
switch (patch 0007): the manual switch is for when the user *wants* to leave
Gemini entirely (e.g., a long-running session); the automatic fallback is
the seamless path when Gemini hits a 429 mid-request and we want OpenCode to
never see the error.

